íŸ@d61f81930eec892551ddcb356e38e107f5d5c167b3c9796bf94076f9d3deddad⁄'Title: title: split words
Path: Examples
Content:
Split the string's words into separate rows.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 'hello world' | split words
‚ï≠‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¨‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚ïÆ
‚îÇ 0 ‚îÇ hello ‚îÇ
‚îÇ 1 ‚îÇ world ‚îÇ
‚ï∞‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¥‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚ïØ


```
Split the string's words, of at least 3 characters, into separate rows.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 'hello to the world' | split words --min-word-length 3
‚ï≠‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¨‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚ïÆ
‚îÇ 0 ‚îÇ hello ‚îÇ
‚îÇ 1 ‚îÇ the   ‚îÇ
‚îÇ 2 ‚îÇ world ‚îÇ
‚ï∞‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¥‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚ïØ


```
A real-world example of splitting words.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> http get https://www.gutenberg.org/files/11/11-0.txt | str downcase | split words --min-word-length 2 | uniq --count | sort-by count --reverse | first 10


```
